# LearnOpenGL

## Introduction
This is a simple starter project to open a window using OpenGL in VSCode to start on https://learnopengl.com

## Prerequisites
List of software and tools required to run the project:
- Visual Studio Code
- CMake
- OpenGL
- GLFW
- GLAD

## Installation
Steps to install the necessary dependencies:
1. Install Visual Studio Code from [here](https://code.visualstudio.com/).
2. Install CMake from [here](https://cmake.org/download/).
3. Download and Integrate GLFW by cloning GLFW into your project
    ```sh
    cd LearnOpenGL/external
    git clone https://github.com/glfw/glfw.git
    ```
4. Download GLAD from [here](https://glad.dav1d.de/) by setting language to c/c++, gl version 3.3 or above, profile to core and extensions empty and press generate. Downlaod the .zip and copy the include and src into LearnOpenGL/external

## Setup
Instructions to set up the project in Visual Studio Code on Windows:
1. Clone the repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/LearnOpenGL.git
    ```
2. Open the project in Visual Studio Code.


## Running the Project
Steps to build and run the project on Windows:
1. Build the project:
    ```sh
    cmake -S . -B build
    cmake --build build
    ```
2. Run the executable:
    ```sh
    .\Debug\LearnOpenGL.exe
    ```

